dv=(y-\theta)^{n-1}\ dy\Rightarrow v=\dfrac{(y-\theta)^n}{n}
 \begin{align} n\int_{y=\theta}^{\theta+1}y(y-\theta)^{n-1}\ dy&=n\left[\left.\dfrac{y(y-\theta)^n}{n}\right|_{y=\theta}^{\theta+1}-\int_{y=\theta}^{\theta+1}\dfrac{(y-\theta)^n}{n} dy\right]\\ &=(\theta+1)-\int_{y=\theta}^{\theta+1}(y-\theta)^{n}\ dy\\ &=(\theta+1)-\left.\dfrac{(y-\theta)^{n+1}}{n+1}\right|_{y=\theta}^{\theta+1}\\ &=(\theta+1)-\dfrac{1}{n+1} \end{align} 
